I=E2=80=99m more convinced than I was coming into the year that the strateg=
y =E2=80=93 investing in hard startups [ https://substack.com/redirect/8769=
f005-6fe2-47b4-adb4-288862e46a4a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZj=
mlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], mainly crypto, bio, and deep tech startups =E2=
=80=93 is the right one, and the right one for Not Boring Capital specifica=
lly.=C2=A0
But as a lot of founders have learned over the past year, a good strategy i=
s necessary but not sufficient. You need the capital to execute it. And not=
 having it is fully on me.=C2=A0
I made the assumption that I=E2=80=99d have enough momentum to raise Fund I=
II quickly, and when that didn=E2=80=99t happen, the process dragged out. T=
he more any fundraising process drags out, the harder it gets. I=E2=80=99ve=
 never felt like I had less leverage or momentum than I have throughout thi=
s process. You can=E2=80=99t manufacture momentum. Especially in a market l=
ike this, people can smell it.=C2=A0
What=E2=80=99s kept me up at night isn=E2=80=99t the lack of leverage or th=
e rejections; it=E2=80=99s the fact that there have been great companies an=
d founders that I=E2=80=99ve wanted to invest in but couldn=E2=80=99t becau=
se I didn=E2=80=99t run a tight process. While I put a ton of time, thought=
, and effort into our investing strategy, and I think it=E2=80=99s the righ=
t one for us, I didn=E2=80=99t put enough into our firm building strategy.
On the bright side, limited funds have also enforced a healthy discipline t=
hat I might not have deeply understood without living through this market. =
We=E2=80=99ve built a very strong early stage portfolio in Fund III, and a =
smaller fund means that it=E2=80=99ll be easier to return capital to LPs. I=
 just think that we=E2=80=99re in one of those rare paradigm shift periods,=
 the biggest yet [ https://substack.com/redirect/78c8f55f-458e-49ef-9aa9-6d=
340a81b86a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU ], and I would like to be deploying more aggressively into it.=C2=A0
Nobody owes you the right to be in market, though. You need to earn it.
There are a bunch of lessons I=E2=80=99ve taken from this process that can =
be boiled down to the idea that to earn the right to manage a fund over the=
 longer term, you need to be good at all aspects of fund management, includ=
ing and maybe especially having capital to deploy when others aren=E2=80=99=
t. There=E2=80=99s no venture capital without capital.=C2=A0
More generally, when momentum is on your side, people focus on your strengt=
hs and forgive your weaknesses. When the momentum stops, they scrutinize th=
e whole thing. This is true for stocks, funds, people, and even essays.=C2=
=A0
That=E2=80=99s good! It=E2=80=99s healthy. It forces you to get fit, to sho=
re up weak points, and to tighten up arguments. It forces you to master you=
r craft.=C2=A0
With the benefit of hindsight, I think the move is to use momentum when you=
