rcumstances.=C2=A0
Personally, I wish that instead of meeting a million people, I=E2=80=99d sp=
ent more time building strong relationships with a handful of people I admi=
re. Instead of investing in hundreds of companies to not miss the winners, =
I wish that I=E2=80=99d focused more on a smaller number that I think will =
really matter. Instead of taking the easier path of being a non-institution=
al fund, I wish I=E2=80=99d spent time meeting with institutional LPs learn=
ing what they look for long before ever trying to raise from them, and rais=
